{"lemma":"غِبْطَةُ","slug":"غِبْطَةُ","root":"غ.ب.ط","root_slug":"غ-ب-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ب-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31376","n31380","n31381"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of غَبَطَ (ḡabaṭa) and غَبِطَ (ḡabiṭa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bliss, beatitude"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"emulation, admiration (endeavor or desire to equal without wishing any harm or loss upon them)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"His Beatitude, a title used for Eastern Churches’ patriarchs","examples":[{"text":"صَاحِبَ ٱلْغِبْطَةِ\nṣāḥiba l-ḡibṭati"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣib.tˤa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31376","headword_ar":"غَبَطَهُ","root":"gbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaboTN","text_ar":"غَبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He felt with his hand his"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a ram's)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloyap","text_ar":"اَلْيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rump,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fat of the tail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order to see if he were fat"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he felt it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(his back)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with his hand in order to know whether he were lean or fat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K: *) and in like manner the verb is used in relation to a she-camel. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gabaTahu","text_ar":"غَبَطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (ISk, Az, S, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gabiTahu","text_ar":"غَبِطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ibn-Buzurj, Sgh, K;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaboTN","text_ar":"غَبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, Az, S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giboTapN","text_ar":"غِبْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or the latter is a simple subst.; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He regarded him"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with unenvious emulation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a wish for the like of his condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, Az, S,) meaning a good condition, (Az,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the like of that which he had attained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for a blessing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and that it might not pass away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without desiring that it should pass away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the latter person:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, Az, S, Msb, K:) the doing so is not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasadN","text_ar":"حَسَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, S, Msb,) for this implies the desire that what is wished for may pass away from its possessor; (Az, Msb;) or it is a kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasad","text_ar":"حَسَد"},{"kind":"text","text":", of a more moderate quality: (Az:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giboTapN","text_ar":"غِبْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaboTN","text_ar":"غَبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"have the signification shown above, and are also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasadN","text_ar":"حَسَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) this latter meaning is assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaboTN","text_ar":"غَبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by IAar; and it is said that the Arabs use"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaboTN","text_ar":"غَبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasadN","text_ar":"حَسَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"metonymically; (TA;) [so that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gabaTahu","text_ar":"غَبَطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gabiTahu","text_ar":"غَبِطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may also mean (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he envied him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; see an ex. in a prov. cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTonN","text_ar":"بَطْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasadN","text_ar":"حَسَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", when it is for courage and the like, is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giboTapN","text_ar":"غِبْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and then it implies admiration, without a wish that the thing admired may pass away from its possessor. (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hsd","text_ar":"حسد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gabaTahu bihi","text_ar":"غَبَطَهُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAth,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He regarded him with a wish for the like of it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning a thing or state which he had attained,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without desiring that it should pass away from the latter person."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, IAth, * Msb.) Mohammad was asked, “ Does"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgaboT","text_ar":"الغَبْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"injure? ” and he answered, “ Yes, like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaboT","text_ar":"الخَبْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"injures: ” or, accord. to the relation of A'Obeyd, “ No, save as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaboT","text_ar":"الخَبْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"injures the [trees called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":": ” (Az, TA:) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaTa","text_ar":"خَبَطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgyT","text_ar":"الغيط"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHasad","text_ar":"الحَسَد"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or a kind thereof, of a more moderate quality; injurious, but not so injurious as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHsd","text_ar":"الحسد"},{"kind":"text","text":"whereby one wishes that a blessing may pass away from his brother;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxbT","text_ar":"الخبط"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the beating off the leaves of trees; after which they become replaced, without there resulting any injury therefrom to the stock and branches: moreover,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgbT","text_ar":"الغبط"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes occasions the smiting of its object with the evil eye. (Az, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giboTapN","text_ar":"غِبْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]       -A3-  Accord. to IKtt,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gabaTa","text_ar":"غَبَطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lied;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but perhaps it is a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaTa","text_ar":"عَبَطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has this meaning; for it is not mentioned by any other. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","ISk","Az","Msb","IAth","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n31380","headword_ar":"غُبْطَةٌ","root":"gbT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A strap in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdap","text_ar":"مَزَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ibn-'Abbád, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iraAk","text_ar":"شِرَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sandal"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Ibn-'Abbád, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is put upon the extremities of the two skins"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereof the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mzAdp","text_ar":"مزادة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is mainly composed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then strongly sewed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn- 'Abbád, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n31381","headword_ar":"غِبْطَةٌ","root":"gbT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state of happiness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of enjoyment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wellbeing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaboTN","text_ar":"غَبْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a gaboTFA laA haboTFA","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ غَبْطًا لَا هَبْطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"we ask of Thee"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a good state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.], (S, K,) and we put our trust in Thee for preservation"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that we may not be brought down from our state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that we may not be abased and humbled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place us in a station for which we may be regarded"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with unenvious emulation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a wish to be in the like condition without its being desired that it should pass away from us,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remove from us the stations of abasement and humiliation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or [we ask of Thee]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exaltation, not humiliation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"increase of"},{"kind":"text","text":"thy"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bounty, not declension nor diminution."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also 1, second sentence.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}